{"questionId":"9066866","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Which is a major product of the electrophilic addition of hydrogen chloride to propene?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A. ClCH<sub>2</sub>CH=CH<sub>2</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B. CH<sub>3</sub>CH(Cl)CH<sub>3</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C. CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>Cl</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D. CH<sub>3</sub>CH=CHCl</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066866","referenceCode":"19M.1.hl.TZ1.33","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which is a major product of the electrophilic addition of hydrogen chloride to propene? A. ClCH2CH=CH2 B. CH3CH(Cl)CH3 C. CH3CH2CH2Cl D. CH3CH=CHCl","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"33","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry","20.1 Types of organic reactions","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}